{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FSfZ9tsX12t3x81ncJzccs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 15-1: CI File Size Gate + Fix Remaining Violations\n     2→\n     3→## Status: done\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want a CI check that fails if any `.ts` file exceeds 300 lines,\n     9→So that file size debt stops accumulating.\n    10→\n    11→<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n    12→\n    13→## Acceptance Criteria\n    14→\n    15→- [x] AC1: Given CI pipeline runs, when any `.ts` file in `src/` (excluding `__tests__/`) exceeds 300 lines, then the build fails with the filename and line count <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [ ] AC2: Given all file splits from Epic 12 are complete, when CI gate is enabled, then it passes (zero violations) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→\n    18→## Technical Notes\n    19→\n    20→**Decision 12 (File Size Enforcement)** and **NFR1** (no file >300 lines excluding tests).\n    21→\n    22→### CI Gate Implementation\n    23→\n    24→Add to `.github/workflows/release.yml` (or a general CI workflow) in the `test` job:\n    25→\n    26→```bash\n    27→# File size gate — fail if any src .ts file exceeds 300 lines (excluding tests)\n    28→violations=$(find src -name '*.ts' -not -path '*__tests__*' -exec awk 'END{if(NR>300)print FILENAME\": \"NR\" lines\"}' {} \\;)\n    29→if [ -n \"$violations\" ]; then\n    30→  echo \"::error::File size violations (>300 lines):\"\n    31→  echo \"$violations\"\n    32→  exit 1\n    33→fi\n    34→```\n    35→\n    36→This runs after `npm run build` so it catches all source files including generated ones.\n    37→\n    38→### Current Violators\n    39→\n    40→As of 2026-03-25, these files exceed 300 lines:\n    41→\n    42→| File | Lines | Notes |\n    43→|------|-------|-------|\n    44→| `src/modules/status/formatters.ts` | 605 | Needs split |\n    45→| `src/modules/sprint/state.ts` | 543 | Needs split |\n    46→| `src/lib/bmad.ts` | 522 | Needs split |\n    47→| `src/lib/scanner.ts` | 447 | Needs split |\n    48→| `src/lib/epic-generator.ts` | 379 | Needs split |\n    49→| `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` | 358 | Needs split |\n    50→| `src/commands/run.ts` | 330 | Needs split |\n    51→| `src/commands/verify.ts` | 314 | Needs split |\n    52→| `src/lib/verifier-session.ts` | 307 | Needs split |\n    53→| `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` | 304 | Needs split |\n    54→| `src/modules/verify/env.ts` | 304 | Needs split |\n    55→\n    56→11 files currently violate the 300-line limit. These are NOT fixed in this story — this story only adds the gate script and CI step. Violations will be addressed by subsequent TD stories. The gate should start in `warn` mode so CI does not block while violations exist.\n    57→\n    58→### Phased Rollout\n    59→\n    60→The gate can start as a warning (exit 0 with annotation) and become a hard failure (exit 1) after violations are resolved. Use a flag or environment variable to control enforcement mode:\n    61→\n    62→```bash\n    63→# Set to 'warn' during transition, 'fail' after all violations resolved\n    64→FILE_SIZE_ENFORCEMENT=\"${FILE_SIZE_ENFORCEMENT:-warn}\"\n    65→```\n    66→\n    67→### Also add NFR5 check: Commands <100 lines\n    68→\n    69→```bash\n    70→violations=$(find src/commands -name '*.ts' -not -path '*__tests__*' -exec awk 'END{if(NR>100)print FILENAME\": \"NR\" lines\"}' {} \\;)\n    71→```\n    72→\n    73→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    74→\n    75→### Task 1: Create `scripts/check-file-sizes.sh` standalone gate script\n    76→- [x] 1.1: Create `scripts/check-file-sizes.sh` with `src/` scan (exclude `__tests__/`, threshold 300 lines)\n    77→- [x] 1.2: Add NFR5 commands check (`src/commands/`, threshold 100 lines)\n    78→- [x] 1.3: Support `FILE_SIZE_ENFORCEMENT` env var (`warn` = exit 0 with annotations, `fail` = exit 1)\n    79→- [x] 1.4: Output GitHub Actions `::error::` annotations for each violation\n    80→- [x] 1.5: Make script executable (`chmod +x`)\n    81→\n    82→### Task 2: Add `lint:sizes` npm script\n    83→- [x] 2.1: Add `\"lint:sizes\": \"bash scripts/check-file-sizes.sh\"` to `package.json` scripts\n    84→\n    85→### Task 3: Integrate into CI workflow\n    86→- [x] 3.1: Add \"File size gate\" step to `.github/workflows/release.yml` `test` job after `npm run build`\n    87→- [x] 3.2: Set `FILE_SIZE_ENFORCEMENT: warn` as env var in CI step (transition mode)\n    88→\n    89→### Task 4: Write tests for the gate script\n    90→- [x] 4.1: Write BATS test that runs `scripts/check-file-sizes.sh` against a temp directory with oversized files and verifies exit code / output\n    91→- [x] 4.2: Write BATS test that verifies `FILE_SIZE_ENFORCEMENT=warn` exits 0 even with violations\n    92→- [x] 4.3: Write BATS test that verifies `FILE_SIZE_ENFORCEMENT=fail` exits 1 with violations\n    93→\n    94→### Task 5: Verify current state\n    95→- [x] 5.1: Run `npm run lint:sizes` locally in warn mode and confirm all violations are reported\n    96→- [x] 5.2: Document remaining violators in session output for future TD stories\n    97→\n    98→## Files to Change\n    99→\n   100→- `scripts/check-file-sizes.sh` — Created. Standalone gate script for CI and local use\n   101→- `.github/workflows/release.yml` — Added file size gate step in `test` job after build\n   102→- `package.json` — Added `lint:sizes` script\n   103→- `tests/check-file-sizes.bats` — Created. 18 BATS tests for the gate script (12 original + 6 added during review)\n   104→\n   105→## Dev Notes\n   106→\n   107→- Gate launches in `warn` mode (AC2 cannot pass yet — 11 violators exist). Switch to `fail` after subsequent TD stories resolve all violations.\n   108→- NFR5 (commands <100 lines) has 15 violators — also warn-only for now.\n   109→- This story is deliberately scoped to the gate mechanism only. File splits are separate stories.\n   110→\n   111→## Dev Agent Record\n   112→\n   113→### Implementation Plan\n   114→\n   115→- Created `scripts/check-file-sizes.sh` as a standalone bash script with two checks: NFR1 (src files <=300 lines) and NFR5 (command files <=100 lines)\n   116→- Script uses `find + awk` to detect oversized files, emits GitHub Actions `::error::` annotations, and supports `FILE_SIZE_ENFORCEMENT` env var for warn/fail mode\n   117→- Added `SRC_DIR` env var override for testability (BATS tests use temp directories)\n   118→- Integrated into CI as a step after `npm run build` in the `test` job, set to `warn` mode during transition\n   119→- 12 BATS tests covering: no violations, NFR1 violations, NFR5 violations, boundary conditions (exact threshold), `__tests__` exclusion, enforcement modes (warn/fail/default), GitHub annotations, combined violations\n   120→\n   121→### Completion Notes\n   122→\n   123→- AC1 is satisfied: the gate detects and reports all violations with filenames and line counts. In `fail` mode it exits 1; in `warn` mode it exits 0 with annotations.\n   124→- AC2 is NOT satisfied yet (expected): 11 NFR1 violators and 15 NFR5 violators exist. This AC will be satisfied after subsequent TD stories split the oversized files.\n   125→- All 319 BATS tests pass (307 existing + 12 new), no regressions.\n   126→\n   127→### Remaining violators for future TD stories\n   128→\n   129→**NFR1 (>300 lines):** `formatters.ts` (605), `state.ts` (543), `bmad.ts` (522), `scanner.ts` (447), `epic-generator.ts` (379), `nodejs.ts` (358), `run.ts` (330), `verify.ts` (314), `verifier-session.ts` (307), `docs-scaffold.ts` (304), `env.ts` (304)\n   130→\n   131→**NFR5 (>100 lines):** `stack.ts` (288), `run.ts` (330), `verify.ts` (314), `retro-import.ts` (298), `teardown.ts` (272), `query.ts` (216), `verify-env.ts` (156), `github-import.ts` (148), `coverage.ts` (139), `state.ts` (131), `bridge.ts` (128), `retry.ts` (126), `audit-action.ts` (119), `sync.ts` (119), `observability-gate.ts` (114)\n   132→\n   133→## Change Log\n   134→\n   135→- 2026-03-25: Created file size gate script, npm script, CI integration, and 12 BATS tests (Story 15-1)\n   136→- 2026-03-25: Code review fixes — added .tsx file support to both NFR1/NFR5 checks, added SRC_DIR sanitization (empty string, trailing slash), added violation summary counts, added 6 new BATS tests (boundary 301/101, .tsx detection, trailing slash, summary counts, combined fail counts). Total: 18 BATS tests. 325 total BATS pass, 143 unit tests pass, 96.97% coverage.\n   137→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01V9Px7PwSDMithH16RuCNBA","session_id":"809dbebc-105d-4f42-bb69-c6ae04307c59","uuid":"864a7028-efd5-4add-9798-904e608f84e6","timestamp":"2026-03-25T01:03:31.660Z"}
