{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CiuKG1VckzzEESZF2gNbGa","type":"tool_result","content":"   356→- This ensures accumulated debt gets addressed before new features start\n   357→\n   358→---\n   359→\n   360→### Decision 7: Error Handling — No More Silent Swallowing\n   361→\n   362→**Problem:** 53 bare `catch {}` blocks. Errors are logged as comments but not propagated. Debugging is impossible because stack traces are lost.\n   363→\n   364→**Decision:** Three error strategies, no fourth:\n   365→\n   366→1. **Result\\<T\\>** for all module-level functions that can fail expectably (file not found, parse error, subprocess failure). Already established — enforce it.\n   367→\n   368→2. **Typed errors** for domain-specific failures:\n   369→```typescript\n   370→class BeadsNotInstalledError extends Error { ... }\n   371→class DockerNotAvailableError extends Error { ... }\n   372→class StateCorruptedError extends Error { ... }\n   373→class StackNotSupportedError extends Error { ... }\n   374→```\n   375→\n   376→3. **Explicit ignore with reason** for truly non-fatal cases:\n   377→```typescript\n   378→try { ... }\n   379→catch {\n   380→  // IGNORE: cleanup failure is non-fatal — container may already be removed\n   381→}\n   382→```\n   383→\n   384→**Banned:** `catch { }`, `catch { return null }`, `catch { /* fallthrough */ }` without an `// IGNORE:` comment explaining why.\n   385→\n   386→**Enforcement:** ESLint rule `no-empty-catch` + custom rule requiring `// IGNORE:` comment in catch blocks that don't rethrow or return Result.fail().\n   387→\n   388→---\n   389→\n   390→### Decision 8: Command Structure — Thin Commands, Fat Modules\n   391→\n   392→**Problem:** `status.ts` is 744 lines. Commands contain business logic (URL builders, formatters, story drill-down). Not testable without command wiring.\n   393→\n   394→**Decision:** Commands are <100 lines. They parse CLI args, call a module function, format output. All business logic lives in modules.\n   395→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01V9Px7PwSDMithH16RuCNBA","session_id":"809dbebc-105d-4f42-bb69-c6ae04307c59","uuid":"880964e5-eda3-4582-90fa-248e6afc5156","timestamp":"2026-03-25T01:04:22.773Z"}
