{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017aTtR5ECH1Wm5oHxNf4xvo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 15-2: ESLint no-empty-catch + Boundary Tests\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want automated enforcement of error handling and module boundaries,\n     9→So that architectural rules aren't just documented but enforced.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given ESLint runs, when a catch block is empty (no `// IGNORE:` comment), then it reports an error <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given a boundary test scans `src/`, when it finds `stack === 'nodejs'` outside `src/lib/stacks/`, then the test fails <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC3: Given a boundary test scans module imports, when a module imports from another module's internal file (not index.ts), then the test fails <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→\n    17→## Technical Notes\n    18→\n    19→**Decision 7 (Error Handling)** and **NFR3/NFR4/NFR6** enforcement.\n    20→\n    21→### ESLint no-empty-catch (AC1)\n    22→\n    23→ESLint's built-in `no-empty` rule catches empty blocks but doesn't require `// IGNORE:` comments. Options:\n    24→\n    25→1. **Use `no-empty` rule** with `allowEmptyCatch: false` (default). This catches `catch {}` but doesn't enforce the comment.\n    26→2. **Custom ESLint rule** that allows catch blocks with `// IGNORE:` comments but fails on truly empty catches or catches with only a comment that doesn't start with `// IGNORE:`.\n    27→\n    28→Recommended: Option 2. Create a local ESLint rule or use `eslint-plugin-local-rules`:\n    29→\n    30→```javascript\n    31→// In eslint config\n    32→rules: {\n    33→  'no-empty': ['error', { allowEmptyCatch: false }],\n    34→  // Plus a custom check that catch blocks either rethrow, return Result.fail(), or have // IGNORE: comment\n    35→}\n    36→```\n    37→\n    38→The 53 existing bare `catch {}` blocks need to be audited. Each must either:\n    39→- Add an `// IGNORE: reason` comment explaining why the error is non-fatal\n    40→- Be converted to `Result.fail()` returns\n    41→- Rethrow the error\n    42→\n    43→### Stack Conditional Boundary Test (AC2)\n    44→\n    45→Create `src/lib/stacks/__tests__/boundary.test.ts` (also referenced in story 10-5):\n    46→\n    47→```typescript\n    48→test('no stack conditionals outside src/lib/stacks/', () => {\n    49→  const srcFiles = glob.sync('src/**/*.ts', { ignore: ['src/lib/stacks/**'] });\n    50→  const violations = srcFiles.filter(file => {\n    51→    const content = readFileSync(file, 'utf-8');\n    52→    return /stack\\s*===\\s*['\"](?:nodejs|python|rust)['\"]/.test(content);\n    53→  });\n    54→  expect(violations).toEqual([]);\n    55→});\n    56→```\n    57→\n    58→### Module Import Boundary Test (AC3)\n    59→\n    60→Create `src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts`:\n    61→\n    62→```typescript\n    63→test('no cross-module internal imports', () => {\n    64→  // Modules: src/modules/*, src/lib/coverage/, src/lib/docker/, etc.\n    65→  // Rule: external consumers import from index.ts only\n    66→  const violations = findCrossModuleInternalImports();\n    67→  expect(violations).toEqual([]);\n    68→});\n    69→```\n    70→\n    71→Check that imports from domain directories use the barrel export (`src/lib/coverage/index.ts`) not internal files (`src/lib/coverage/parser.ts`).\n    72→\n    73→### NFR enforcement mapping\n    74→\n    75→| NFR | Enforcement | Location |\n    76→|-----|-------------|----------|\n    77→| NFR3 | ESLint no-empty-catch | `.eslintrc` or `eslint.config.js` |\n    78→| NFR4 | Boundary test | `src/lib/stacks/__tests__/boundary.test.ts` |\n    79→| NFR6 | Boundary test | `src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts` |\n    80→\n    81→## Files to Change\n    82→\n    83→- `.eslintrc.json` or `eslint.config.js` — Add/configure `no-empty` rule with `allowEmptyCatch: false`. Add custom rule if using local rules plugin\n    84→- `src/lib/stacks/__tests__/boundary.test.ts` — Create. Test that no stack conditionals exist outside `src/lib/stacks/`\n    85→- `src/__tests__/boundaries.test.ts` — Create. Test that module imports only go through index.ts facades\n    86→- All files with bare `catch {}` blocks — Audit and add `// IGNORE:` comments or convert to proper error handling (53 locations)\n    87→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01V9Px7PwSDMithH16RuCNBA","session_id":"809dbebc-105d-4f42-bb69-c6ae04307c59","uuid":"486f1ef2-604e-4c6d-9aa6-538fb22e2fde","timestamp":"2026-03-25T01:04:41.106Z"}
